4252 MemOperand MacroAssembler::ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
4253  ExternalReference reference, Register scratch) {
4254  if (root_array_available()) {
4255  if (reference.IsIsolateFieldId()) {
4256  return MemOperand(kRootRegister, reference.offset_from_root_register());
4257  }
4258  if (options().enable_root_relative_access) {
4259  int64_t offset =
4260  RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReference(isolate(), reference);
4261  if (is_int32(offset)) {
4262  return MemOperand(kRootRegister, static_cast<int32_t>(offset));
4263  }
4264  }
4265  if (root_array_available_ && options().isolate_independent_code) {
4266  if (IsAddressableThroughRootRegister(isolate(), reference)) {
4267  // Some external references can be efficiently loaded as an offset from
4268  // kRootRegister.
4269  intptr_t offset =
4270  RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReference(isolate(), reference);
4271  CHECK(is_int32(offset));
4272  return MemOperand(kRootRegister, static_cast<int32_t>(offset));
4273  } else {
4274  // Otherwise, do a memory load from the external reference table.
4275  DCHECK(scratch.is_valid());
4276  Ld(scratch, MemOperand(kRootRegister,
4277  RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReferenceTableEntry(
4278  isolate(), reference)));
4279  return MemOperand(scratch, 0);
4280  }
4281  }
4282  }
4283  DCHECK(scratch.is_valid());
4284  li(scratch, reference);
4285  return MemOperand(scratch, 0);
4286 }

4288 void MacroAssembler::Jump(Register target, Condition cond, Register rs,
4289  const Operand& rt, BranchDelaySlot bd) {
4290  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4291  if (kArchVariant == kMips64r6 && bd == PROTECT) {
4292  if (cond == cc_always) {
4293  jic(target, 0);
4294  } else {
4295  BRANCH_ARGS_CHECK(cond, rs, rt);
4296  Branch(2, NegateCondition(cond), rs, rt);
4297  jic(target, 0);
4298  }
4299  } else {
4300  if (cond == cc_always) {
4301  jr(target);
4302  } else {
4303  BRANCH_ARGS_CHECK(cond, rs, rt);
4304  Branch(2, NegateCondition(cond), rs, rt);
4305  jr(target);
4306  }
4307  // Emit a nop in the branch delay slot if required.
4308  if (bd == PROTECT) nop();
4309  }
4310 }

4312 void MacroAssembler::Jump(intptr_t target, RelocInfo::Mode rmode,
4313  Condition cond, Register rs, const Operand& rt,
4314  BranchDelaySlot bd) {
4315  Label skip;
4316  if (cond != cc_always) {
4317  Branch(USE_DELAY_SLOT, &skip, NegateCondition(cond), rs, rt);
4318  }
4319  // The first instruction of 'li' may be placed in the delay slot.
4320  // This is not an issue, t9 is expected to be clobbered anyway.
4321  {
4322  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4323  li(t9, Operand(target, rmode));
4324  Jump(t9, al, zero_reg, Operand(zero_reg), bd);
4325  bind(&skip);
4326  }
4327 }

4335 void MacroAssembler::Jump(Handle<Code> code, RelocInfo::Mode rmode,

4361 // Note: To call gcc-compiled C code on mips, you must call through t9.
4362 void MacroAssembler::Call(Register target, Condition cond, Register rs,
4363  const Operand& rt, BranchDelaySlot bd) {
4364  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4365  if (kArchVariant == kMips64r6 && bd == PROTECT) {
4366  if (cond == cc_always) {
4367  jialc(target, 0);
4368  } else {
4369  BRANCH_ARGS_CHECK(cond, rs, rt);
4370  Branch(2, NegateCondition(cond), rs, rt);
4371  jialc(target, 0);
4372  }
4373  } else {
4374  if (cond == cc_always) {
4375  jalr(target);
4376  } else {
4377  BRANCH_ARGS_CHECK(cond, rs, rt);
4378  Branch(2, NegateCondition(cond), rs, rt);
4379  jalr(target);
4380  }
4381  // Emit a nop in the branch delay slot if required.
4382  if (bd == PROTECT) nop();
4383  }
4384  set_pc_for_safepoint();
4385 }

4396  } else {
4397  Branch(on_in_range, ls, value, Operand(higher_limit - lower_limit));
4398  }

4449 void MacroAssembler::CallBuiltin(Builtin builtin) {
4450  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(this, CommentForOffHeapTrampoline("call", builtin));
4451  Register temp = t9;
4452  switch (options().builtin_call_jump_mode) {
4453  case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kAbsolute: {
4454  li(temp, Operand(BuiltinEntry(builtin), RelocInfo::OFF_HEAP_TARGET));
4455  Call(temp);
4456  break;
4457  }
4458  case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kIndirect: {
4459  LoadEntryFromBuiltin(builtin, temp);
4460  Call(temp);
4461  break;
4462  }
4463  case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kForMksnapshot: {
4464  Handle<Code> code = isolate()->builtins()->code_handle(builtin);
4465  IndirectLoadConstant(temp, code);
4466  CallCodeObject(temp, kJSEntrypointTag);
4467  break;
4468  }
4469  case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kPCRelative:
4470  // Short builtin calls is unsupported in mips64.
4471  UNREACHABLE();
4472  }
4473 }

4514 void MacroAssembler::PatchAndJump(Address target) {
4515  if (kArchVariant != kMips64r6) {
4516  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4517  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4518  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4519  mov(scratch, ra);
4520  bal(1); // jump to ld
4521  nop(); // in the delay slot
4522  ld(t9, MemOperand(ra, kInstrSize * 3)); // ra == pc_
4523  jr(t9);
4524  mov(ra, scratch); // in delay slot
4525  DCHECK_EQ(reinterpret_cast<uint64_t>(pc_) % 8, 0);
4526  *reinterpret_cast<uint64_t*>(pc_) = target; // pc_ should be align.
4527  pc_ += sizeof(uint64_t);
4528  } else {
4529  // TODO(mips r6): Implement.
4530  UNIMPLEMENTED();
4531  }
4532 }
4533 
4534 void MacroAssembler::StoreReturnAddressAndCall(Register target) {
4535  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4536  // This generates the final instruction sequence for calls to C functions
4537  // once an exit frame has been constructed.
4538  //
4539  // Note that this assumes the caller code (i.e. the InstructionStream object
4540  // currently being generated) is immovable or that the callee function cannot
4541  // trigger GC, since the callee function will return to it.
4542 
4543  // Compute the return address in lr to return to after the jump below. The pc
4544  // is already at '+ 8' from the current instruction; but return is after three
4545  // instructions, so add another 4 to pc to get the return address.
4546 
4547  Assembler::BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4548  static constexpr int kNumInstructionsToJump = 4;
4549  Label find_ra;
4550  // Adjust the value in ra to point to the correct return location, 2nd
4551  // instruction past the real call into C code (the jalr(t9)), and push it.
4552  // This is the return address of the exit frame.
4553  if (kArchVariant >= kMips64r6) {
4554  addiupc(ra, kNumInstructionsToJump + 1);
4555  } else {
4556  // This no-op-and-link sequence saves PC + 8 in ra register on pre-r6 MIPS
4557  nal(); // nal has branch delay slot.
4558  Daddu(ra, ra, kNumInstructionsToJump * kInstrSize);
4559  }
4560  bind(&find_ra);
4561 
4562  // This spot was reserved in EnterExitFrame.
4563  Sd(ra, MemOperand(sp));
4564  // Stack space reservation moved to the branch delay slot below.
4565  // Stack is still aligned.
4566 
4567  // Call the C routine.
4568  mov(t9, target); // Function pointer to t9 to conform to ABI for PIC.
4569  jalr(t9);
4570  // Set up sp in the delay slot.
4571  daddiu(sp, sp, -kCArgsSlotsSize);
4572  // Make sure the stored 'ra' points to this position.
4573  DCHECK_EQ(kNumInstructionsToJump, InstructionsGeneratedSince(&find_ra));
4574 }

4576 void MacroAssembler::Ret(Condition cond, Register rs, const Operand& rt,
4577  BranchDelaySlot bd) {
4578  Jump(ra, cond, rs, rt, bd);
4579 }

4581 void MacroAssembler::BranchLong(Label* L, BranchDelaySlot bdslot) {
4582  if (kArchVariant == kMips64r6 && bdslot == PROTECT &&
4583  (!L->is_bound() || is_near_r6(L))) {
4584  BranchShortHelperR6(0, L);
4585  } else {
4586  // Generate position independent long branch.
4587  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4588  int64_t imm64 = branch_long_offset(L);
4589  DCHECK(is_int32(imm64));
4590  int32_t imm32 = static_cast<int32_t>(imm64);
4591  or_(t8, ra, zero_reg);
4592  nal(); // Read PC into ra register.
4593  lui(t9, (imm32 & kHiMaskOf32) >> kLuiShift); // Branch delay slot.
4594  ori(t9, t9, (imm32 & kImm16Mask));
4595  daddu(t9, ra, t9);
4596  if (bdslot == USE_DELAY_SLOT) {
4597  or_(ra, t8, zero_reg);
4598  }
4599  jr(t9);
4600  // Emit a or_ in the branch delay slot if it's protected.
4601  if (bdslot == PROTECT) or_(ra, t8, zero_reg);
4602  }
4603 }
4604 
4605 void MacroAssembler::BranchLong(int32_t offset, BranchDelaySlot bdslot) {
4606  if (kArchVariant == kMips64r6 && bdslot == PROTECT && (is_int26(offset))) {
4607  BranchShortHelperR6(offset, nullptr);
4608  } else {
4609  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4610  or_(t8, ra, zero_reg);
4611  nal(); // Read PC into ra register.
4612  lui(t9, (offset & kHiMaskOf32) >> kLuiShift); // Branch delay slot.
4613  ori(t9, t9, (offset & kImm16Mask));
4614  daddu(t9, ra, t9);
4615  if (bdslot == USE_DELAY_SLOT) {
4616  or_(ra, t8, zero_reg);
4617  }
4618  jr(t9);
4619  // Emit a or_ in the branch delay slot if it's protected.
4620  if (bdslot == PROTECT) or_(ra, t8, zero_reg);
4621  }
4622 }

4624 void MacroAssembler::BranchAndLinkLong(Label* L, BranchDelaySlot bdslot) {
4625  if (kArchVariant == kMips64r6 && bdslot == PROTECT &&

4751 void MacroAssembler::PushArray(Register array, Register size, Register scratch,
4752  Register scratch2, PushArrayOrder order) {
4753  DCHECK(!AreAliased(array, size, scratch, scratch2));
4754  Label loop, entry;
4755  if (order == PushArrayOrder::kReverse) {
4756  mov(scratch, zero_reg);
4757  jmp(&entry);
4758  bind(&loop);
4759  Dlsa(scratch2, array, scratch, kPointerSizeLog2);
4760  Ld(scratch2, MemOperand(scratch2));
4761  push(scratch2);
4762  Daddu(scratch, scratch, Operand(1));
4763  bind(&entry);
4764  Branch(&loop, less, scratch, Operand(size));
4765  } else {
4766  mov(scratch, size);
4767  jmp(&entry);
4768  bind(&loop);
4769  Dlsa(scratch2, array, scratch, kPointerSizeLog2);
4770  Ld(scratch2, MemOperand(scratch2));
4771  push(scratch2);
4772  bind(&entry);
4773  Daddu(scratch, scratch, Operand(-1));
4774  Branch(&loop, greater_equal, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
4775  }
4776 }

4781 void MacroAssembler::PushStackHandler() {
4782  // Adjust this code if not the case.
4783  static_assert(StackHandlerConstants::kSize == 2 * kPointerSize);
4784  static_assert(StackHandlerConstants::kNextOffset == 0 * kPointerSize);
4785 
4786  Push(Smi::zero()); // Padding.
4787 
4788  // Link the current handler as the next handler.
4789  li(t2,
4790  ExternalReference::Create(IsolateAddressId::kHandlerAddress, isolate()));
4791  Ld(t1, MemOperand(t2));
4792  push(t1);
4793 
4794  // Set this new handler as the current one.
4795  Sd(sp, MemOperand(t2));
4796 }
4797 
4798 void MacroAssembler::PopStackHandler() {
4799  static_assert(StackHandlerConstants::kNextOffset == 0);
4800  pop(a1);
4801  Daddu(sp, sp,
4802  Operand(
4803  static_cast<int64_t>(StackHandlerConstants::kSize - kPointerSize)));
4804  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4805  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4806  li(scratch,
4807  ExternalReference::Create(IsolateAddressId::kHandlerAddress, isolate()));
4808  Sd(a1, MemOperand(scratch));
4809 }

4900 void MacroAssembler::StackOverflowCheck(Register num_args, Register scratch1,
4901  Register scratch2,
4902  Label* stack_overflow) {
4903  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4904  // Check the stack for overflow. We are not trying to catch
4905  // interruptions (e.g. debug break and preemption) here, so the "real stack
4906  // limit" is checked.
4907 
4908  LoadStackLimit(scratch1, StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit);
4909  // Make scratch1 the space we have left. The stack might already be overflowed
4910  // here which will cause scratch1 to become negative.
4911  dsubu(scratch1, sp, scratch1);
4912  // Check if the arguments will overflow the stack.
4913  dsll(scratch2, num_args, kPointerSizeLog2);
4914  // Signed comparison.
4915  Branch(stack_overflow, le, scratch1, Operand(scratch2));
4916 }

4929  dsll(destination, index, kJSDispatchTableEntrySizeLog2);
4930  Daddu(scratch, scratch, destination);
4931  Ld(destination, MemOperand(scratch, JSDispatchEntry::kEntrypointOffset));

4978 
4979 void MacroAssembler::InvokePrologue(Register expected_parameter_count,
4980  Register actual_parameter_count,
4981  InvokeType type) {
4982  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4983  Label regular_invoke;
4984 
4985  // a0: actual arguments count
4986  // a1: function (passed through to callee)
4987  // a2: expected arguments count
4988 
4989  DCHECK_EQ(actual_parameter_count, a0);
4990  DCHECK_EQ(expected_parameter_count, a2);
4991 
4992  // If overapplication or if the actual argument count is equal to the
4993  // formal parameter count, no need to push extra undefined values.
4994  Dsubu(expected_parameter_count, expected_parameter_count,
4995  actual_parameter_count);
4996  Branch(&regular_invoke, le, expected_parameter_count, Operand(zero_reg));
4997 
4998  Label stack_overflow;
4999  StackOverflowCheck(expected_parameter_count, t0, t1, &stack_overflow);
5000  // Underapplication. Move the arguments already in the stack, including the
5001  // receiver and the return address.
5002  {
5003  Label copy;
5004  Register src = a6, dest = a7;
5005  mov(src, sp);
5006  dsll(t0, expected_parameter_count, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
5007  Dsubu(sp, sp, Operand(t0));
5008  // Update stack pointer.
5009  mov(dest, sp);
5010  mov(t0, actual_parameter_count);
5011  bind(&copy);
5012  Ld(t1, MemOperand(src, 0));
5013  Sd(t1, MemOperand(dest, 0));
5014  Dsubu(t0, t0, Operand(1));
5015  Daddu(src, src, Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
5016  Daddu(dest, dest, Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
5017  Branch(&copy, gt, t0, Operand(zero_reg));
5018  }
5019 
5020  // Fill remaining expected arguments with undefined values.
5021  LoadRoot(t0, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
5022  {
5023  Label loop;
5024  bind(&loop);
5025  Sd(t0, MemOperand(a7, 0));
5026  Dsubu(expected_parameter_count, expected_parameter_count, Operand(1));
5027  Daddu(a7, a7, Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
5028  Branch(&loop, gt, expected_parameter_count, Operand(zero_reg));
5029  }
5030  b(&regular_invoke);
5031  nop();
5032 
5033  bind(&stack_overflow);
5034  {
5035  FrameScope frame(
5036  this, has_frame() ? StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE : StackFrame::INTERNAL);
5037  CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowStackOverflow);
5038  break_(0xCC);
5039  }
5040 
5041  bind(&regular_invoke);
5042 }
5043 
5044 void MacroAssembler::CheckDebugHook(
5045  Register fun, Register new_target,
5046  Register expected_parameter_count_or_dispatch_handle,
5047  Register actual_parameter_count) {
5048  DCHECK(!AreAliased(t0, fun, new_target,
5049  expected_parameter_count_or_dispatch_handle,
5050  actual_parameter_count));
5051  Label skip_hook;
5052 
5053  li(t0, ExternalReference::debug_hook_on_function_call_address(isolate()));
5054  Lb(t0, MemOperand(t0));
5055  Branch(&skip_hook, eq, t0, Operand(zero_reg));
5056  {
5057  // Load receiver to pass it later to DebugOnFunctionCall hook.
5058  LoadReceiver(t0);
5059  FrameScope frame(
5060  this, has_frame() ? StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE : StackFrame::INTERNAL);
5061  SmiTag(expected_parameter_count_or_dispatch_handle);
5062  SmiTag(actual_parameter_count);
5063  Push(expected_parameter_count_or_dispatch_handle, actual_parameter_count);
5064  if (new_target.is_valid()) {
5065  Push(new_target);
5066  }
5067  Push(fun, fun, t0);
5068  CallRuntime(Runtime::kDebugOnFunctionCall);
5069  Pop(fun);
5070  if (new_target.is_valid()) {
5071  Pop(new_target);
5072  }
5073 
5074  Pop(expected_parameter_count_or_dispatch_handle, actual_parameter_count);
5075  SmiUntag(actual_parameter_count);
5076 
5077  SmiUntag(expected_parameter_count_or_dispatch_handle);
5078  }
5079  bind(&skip_hook);
5080 }

5084  Register function, Register actual_parameter_count, InvokeType type,
5085  ArgumentAdaptionMode argument_adaption_mode) {
5086  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);

5088  DCHECK(type == InvokeType::kJump || has_frame());
5089 
5090  // Contract with called JS functions requires that function is passed in a1.
5091  // (See FullCodeGenerator::Generate().)
5092  DCHECK_EQ(function, a1);
5093 
5094  // Set up the context.
5095  Ld(cp, FieldMemOperand(function, JSFunction::kContextOffset));
5096

5098  argument_adaption_mode);
5099 }

5117 void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunctionCode(
5118  Register function, Register new_target, Register actual_parameter_count,
5119  InvokeType type, ArgumentAdaptionMode argument_adaption_mode) {
5120  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5121  // You can't call a function without a valid frame.
5122  DCHECK_IMPLIES(type == InvokeType::kCall, has_frame());
5123  DCHECK_EQ(function, a1);
5124  DCHECK_IMPLIES(new_target.is_valid(), new_target == a3);
5125 
5126  Register dispatch_handle = kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister;
5127  Lw(dispatch_handle,
5128  FieldMemOperand(function, JSFunction::kDispatchHandleOffset));
5129 
5130  // On function call, call into the debugger if necessary.
5131  Label debug_hook, continue_after_hook;
5132  {
5133  li(t0, ExternalReference::debug_hook_on_function_call_address(isolate()));
5134  Lb(t0, MemOperand(t0, 0));
5135  BranchShort(&debug_hook, ne, t0, Operand(zero_reg));
5136  }
5137  bind(&continue_after_hook);
5138 
5139  // Clear the new.target register if not given.
5140  if (!new_target.is_valid()) {
5141  LoadRoot(a3, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
5142  }
5143 
5144  Register scratch = s1;
5145  if (argument_adaption_mode == ArgumentAdaptionMode::kAdapt) {
5146  Register expected_parameter_count = a2;
5147  LoadParameterCountFromJSDispatchTable(expected_parameter_count,
5148  dispatch_handle, scratch);
5149  InvokePrologue(expected_parameter_count, actual_parameter_count, type);
5150  }
5151 
5152  // We call indirectly through the code field in the function to
5153  // allow recompilation to take effect without changing any of the
5154  // call sites.
5155  LoadEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister,
5156  dispatch_handle, scratch);
5157  switch (type) {
5158  case InvokeType::kCall:
5159  Call(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister);
5160  break;
5161  case InvokeType::kJump:
5162  Jump(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister);
5163  break;
5164  }
5165  Label done;
5166  Branch(&done);
5167 
5168  // Deferred debug hook.
5169  bind(&debug_hook);
5170  CheckDebugHook(function, new_target, dispatch_handle, actual_parameter_count);
5171  Branch(&continue_after_hook);
5172 
5173  bind(&done);
5174 }
5175 #else
5176 void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunctionCode(Register function, Register new_target,
5177  Register expected_parameter_count,
5178  Register actual_parameter_count,
5179  InvokeType type) {
5180  // You can't call a function without a valid frame.
5181  DCHECK_IMPLIES(type == InvokeType::kCall, has_frame());
5182  DCHECK_EQ(function, a1);
5183  DCHECK_IMPLIES(new_target.is_valid(), new_target == a3);
5184 
5185  // On function call, call into the debugger if necessary.
5186  CheckDebugHook(function, new_target, expected_parameter_count,
5187  actual_parameter_count);
5188 
5189  // Clear the new.target register if not given.
5190  if (!new_target.is_valid()) {
5191  LoadRoot(a3, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
5192  }
5193 
5194  InvokePrologue(expected_parameter_count, actual_parameter_count, type);
5195  // We call indirectly through the code field in the function to
5196  // allow recompilation to take effect without changing any of the
5197  // call sites.
5198  constexpr int unused_argument_count = 0;
5199  switch (type) {
5200  case InvokeType::kCall:
5201  CallJSFunction(function, unused_argument_count);
5202  break;
5203  case InvokeType::kJump:
5204  JumpJSFunction(function);
5205  break;
5206  }
5207  Label done;
5208  // Continue here if InvokePrologue does handle the invocation due to
5209  // mismatched parameter counts.
5210  bind(&done);
5211 }

5272 void MacroAssembler::DaddOverflow(Register dst, Register left,
5273  const Operand& right, Register overflow) {
5274  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5275  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5276  Register right_reg = no_reg;
5277  Register scratch = t8;
5278  if (!right.is_reg()) {
5279  li(at, Operand(right));
5280  right_reg = at;
5281  } else {
5282  right_reg = right.rm();
5283  }
5284 
5285  DCHECK(left != scratch && right_reg != scratch && dst != scratch &&
5286  overflow != scratch);
5287  DCHECK(overflow != left && overflow != right_reg);
5288 
5289  if (dst == left || dst == right_reg) {
5290  daddu(scratch, left, right_reg);
5291  xor_(overflow, scratch, left);
5292  xor_(at, scratch, right_reg);
5293  and_(overflow, overflow, at);
5294  mov(dst, scratch);
5295  } else {
5296  daddu(dst, left, right_reg);
5297  xor_(overflow, dst, left);
5298  xor_(at, dst, right_reg);
5299  and_(overflow, overflow, at);
5300  }
5301 }

5304  const Operand& right, Register overflow) {
5305  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5306  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5307  Register right_reg = no_reg;
5308  Register scratch = t8;
5309  if (!right.is_reg()) {
5310  li(at, Operand(right));
5311  right_reg = at;
5312  } else {
5313  right_reg = right.rm();
5314  }
5315 
5316  DCHECK(left != scratch && right_reg != scratch && dst != scratch &&
5317  overflow != scratch);
5318  DCHECK(overflow != left && overflow != right_reg);
5319 
5320  if (dst == left || dst == right_reg) {
5321  dsubu(scratch, left, right_reg);
5322  xor_(overflow, left, scratch);
5323  xor_(at, left, right_reg);
5324  and_(overflow, overflow, at);
5325  mov(dst, scratch);
5326  } else {
5327  dsubu(dst, left, right_reg);
5328  xor_(overflow, left, dst);
5329  xor_(at, left, right_reg);

5334 void MacroAssembler::MulOverflow(Register dst, Register left,
5335  const Operand& right, Register overflow) {
5336  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5337  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5338  Register right_reg = no_reg;
5339  Register scratch = t8;
5340  if (!right.is_reg()) {
5341  li(at, Operand(right));
5342  right_reg = at;
5343  } else {
5344  right_reg = right.rm();
5345  }
5346 
5347  DCHECK(left != scratch && right_reg != scratch && dst != scratch &&
5348  overflow != scratch);
5349  DCHECK(overflow != left && overflow != right_reg);
5350 
5351  if (dst == left || dst == right_reg) {
5352  Mul(scratch, left, right_reg);
5353  Mulh(overflow, left, right_reg);
5354  mov(dst, scratch);
5355  } else {
5356  Mul(dst, left, right_reg);
5357  Mulh(overflow, left, right_reg);
5358  }
5359 
5360  dsra32(scratch, dst, 0);
5361  xor_(overflow, overflow, scratch);

5364 void MacroAssembler::DMulOverflow(Register dst, Register left,
5365  const Operand& right, Register overflow) {
5366  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5367  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5368  Register right_reg = no_reg;
5369  Register scratch = t8;
5370  if (!right.is_reg()) {
5371  li(at, Operand(right));
5372  right_reg = at;
5373  } else {
5374  right_reg = right.rm();
5375  }
5376 
5377  DCHECK(left != scratch && right_reg != scratch && dst != scratch &&
5378  overflow != scratch);
5379  DCHECK(overflow != left && overflow != right_reg);
5380 
5381  if (dst == left || dst == right_reg) {
5382  Dmul(scratch, left, right_reg);
5383  Dmulh(overflow, left, right_reg);
5384  mov(dst, scratch);
5385  } else {
5386  Dmul(dst, left, right_reg);
5387  Dmulh(overflow, left, right_reg);
5388  }
5389 
5390  dsra32(scratch, dst, 31);
5391  xor_(overflow, overflow, scratch);
5392 }
5393 
5394 void MacroAssembler::CallRuntime(const Runtime::Function* f,
5395  int num_arguments) {
5396  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5397  // All parameters are on the stack. v0 has the return value after call.
5398 
5399  // If the expected number of arguments of the runtime function is
5400  // constant, we check that the actual number of arguments match the
5401  // expectation.
5402  CHECK(f->nargs < 0 || f->nargs == num_arguments);
5403 
5404  // TODO(1236192): Most runtime routines don't need the number of
5405  // arguments passed in because it is constant. At some point we
5406  // should remove this need and make the runtime routine entry code
5407  // smarter.
5408  PrepareCEntryArgs(num_arguments);
5409  PrepareCEntryFunction(ExternalReference::Create(f));
5410  bool switch_to_central_stack = options().is_wasm;
5411  CallBuiltin(Builtins::RuntimeCEntry(f->result_size, switch_to_central_stack));
5412 }
5413 
5414 void MacroAssembler::TailCallRuntime(Runtime::FunctionId fid) {
5415  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5416  const Runtime::Function* function = Runtime::FunctionForId(fid);
5417  DCHECK_EQ(1, function->result_size);
5418  if (function->nargs >= 0) {
5419  PrepareCEntryArgs(function->nargs);
5420  }
5421  JumpToExternalReference(ExternalReference::Create(fid));
5422 }
5423 
5424 void MacroAssembler::JumpToExternalReference(const ExternalReference& builtin,
5425  bool builtin_exit_frame) {
5426  PrepareCEntryFunction(builtin);
5427  TailCallBuiltin(Builtins::CEntry(1, ArgvMode::kStack, builtin_exit_frame));
5428 }

5432  Branch(target_if_cleared, eq, in, Operand(kClearedWeakHeapObjectLower32));

5435 }

5437 void MacroAssembler::EmitIncrementCounter(StatsCounter* counter, int value,
5438  Register scratch1,
5439  Register scratch2) {
5440  DCHECK_GT(value, 0);
5441  if (v8_flags.native_code_counters && counter->Enabled()) {
5442  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5443  // This operation has to be exactly 32-bit wide in case the external
5444  // reference table redirects the counter to a uint32_t dummy_stats_counter_
5445  // field.
5446  li(scratch2, ExternalReference::Create(counter));
5447  Lw(scratch1, MemOperand(scratch2));
5448  Addu(scratch1, scratch1, Operand(value));
5449  Sw(scratch1, MemOperand(scratch2));
5450  }
5451 }
5452 
5453 void MacroAssembler::EmitDecrementCounter(StatsCounter* counter, int value,
5454  Register scratch1,
5455  Register scratch2) {
5456  DCHECK_GT(value, 0);
5457  if (v8_flags.native_code_counters && counter->Enabled()) {
5458  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5459  // This operation has to be exactly 32-bit wide in case the external
5460  // reference table redirects the counter to a uint32_t dummy_stats_counter_
5461  // field.
5462  li(scratch2, ExternalReference::Create(counter));
5463  Lw(scratch1, MemOperand(scratch2));
5464  Subu(scratch1, scratch1, Operand(value));
5465  Sw(scratch1, MemOperand(scratch2));
5466  }
5467 }

5475 void MacroAssembler::Check(Condition cc, AbortReason reason, Register rs,
5476  Operand rt) {
5477  Label L;
5478  Branch(&L, cc, rs, rt);
5479  Abort(reason);
5480  // Will not return here.
5481  bind(&L);
5482 }
5483 void MacroAssembler::SbxCheck(Condition cc, AbortReason reason, Register rj,
5484  Operand rk) {
5485  Check(cc, reason, rj, rk);
5486 }
5487 void MacroAssembler::Abort(AbortReason reason) {
5488  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5489  if (v8_flags.code_comments) {
5490  RecordComment("Abort message:", SourceLocation{});
5491  RecordComment(GetAbortReason(reason), SourceLocation{});
5492  }
5493 
5494  // Without debug code, save the code size and just trap.
5495  if (!v8_flags.debug_code || v8_flags.trap_on_abort) {
5496  stop();
5497  return;
5498  }
5499 
5500  if (should_abort_hard()) {
5501  // We don't care if we constructed a frame. Just pretend we did.
5502  FrameScope assume_frame(this, StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE);
5503  PrepareCallCFunction(1, a0);
5504  li(a0, Operand(static_cast<int>(reason)));
5505  li(a1, ExternalReference::abort_with_reason());
5506  // Use Call directly to avoid any unneeded overhead. The function won't
5507  // return anyway.
5508  Call(a1);
5509  return;
5510  }
5511 
5512  Label abort_start;
5513  bind(&abort_start);
5514 
5515  Move(a0, Smi::FromInt(static_cast<int>(reason)));
5516 
5517  {
5518  // We don't actually want to generate a pile of code for this, so just
5519  // claim there is a stack frame, without generating one.
5520  FrameScope scope(this, StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE);
5521  if (root_array_available()) {
5522  // Generate an indirect call via builtins entry table here in order to
5523  // ensure that the interpreter_entry_return_pc_offset is the same for
5524  // InterpreterEntryTrampoline and InterpreterEntryTrampolineForProfiling
5525  // when v8_flags.debug_code is enabled.
5526  LoadEntryFromBuiltin(Builtin::kAbort, t9);
5527  Call(t9);
5528  } else {
5529  CallBuiltin(Builtin::kAbort);
5530  }
5531  }
5532  // Will not return here.
5533  if (is_trampoline_pool_blocked()) {
5534  // If the calling code cares about the exact number of
5535  // instructions generated, we insert padding here to keep the size
5536  // of the Abort macro constant.
5537  // Currently in debug mode with debug_code enabled the number of
5538  // generated instructions is 10, so we use this as a maximum value.
5539  static const int kExpectedAbortInstructions = 10;
5540  int abort_instructions = InstructionsGeneratedSince(&abort_start);
5541  DCHECK_LE(abort_instructions, kExpectedAbortInstructions);
5542  while (abort_instructions++ < kExpectedAbortInstructions) {
5543  nop();
5544  }
5545  }
5546 }
5547 
5548 void MacroAssembler::LoadMap(Register destination, Register object) {

5550 }

5552 void MacroAssembler::LoadFeedbackVector(Register dst, Register closure,
5553  Register scratch, Label* fbv_undef) {
5554  Label done;
5555  // Load the feedback vector from the closure.
5556  Ld(dst, FieldMemOperand(closure, JSFunction::kFeedbackCellOffset));
5557  Ld(dst, FieldMemOperand(dst, FeedbackCell::kValueOffset));
5558 
5559  // Check if feedback vector is valid.
5560  Ld(scratch, FieldMemOperand(dst, HeapObject::kMapOffset));
5561  Lhu(scratch, FieldMemOperand(scratch, Map::kInstanceTypeOffset));
5562  Branch(&done, eq, scratch, Operand(FEEDBACK_VECTOR_TYPE));
5563 
5564  // Not valid, load undefined.
5565  LoadRoot(dst, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
5566  Branch(fbv_undef);
5567 
5568  bind(&done);
5569 }

5587 void MacroAssembler::EnterFrame(StackFrame::Type type) {
5588  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5589  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5590  Push(ra, fp);
5591  Move(fp, sp);
5592  if (!StackFrame::IsJavaScript(type)) {
5593  li(kScratchReg, Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(type)));
5594  Push(kScratchReg);
5595  }
5596 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY

5598  Push(kWasmImplicitArgRegister);

5603 void MacroAssembler::LeaveFrame(StackFrame::Type type) {
5604  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5605  daddiu(sp, fp, 2 * kPointerSize);
5606  Ld(ra, MemOperand(fp, 1 * kPointerSize));
5607  Ld(fp, MemOperand(fp, 0 * kPointerSize));
5608 }
5609 
5610 void MacroAssembler::EnterExitFrame(Register scratch, int stack_space,
5611  StackFrame::Type frame_type) {
5612  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5613  DCHECK(frame_type == StackFrame::EXIT ||
5614  frame_type == StackFrame::BUILTIN_EXIT ||
5615  frame_type == StackFrame::API_ACCESSOR_EXIT ||
5616  frame_type == StackFrame::API_CALLBACK_EXIT);
5617 
5618  using ER = ExternalReference;
5619 
5620  // Set up the frame structure on the stack.
5621  static_assert(2 * kPointerSize == ExitFrameConstants::kCallerSPDisplacement);
5622  static_assert(1 * kPointerSize == ExitFrameConstants::kCallerPCOffset);
5623  static_assert(0 * kPointerSize == ExitFrameConstants::kCallerFPOffset);
5624 
5625  // This is how the stack will look:
5626  // fp + 2 (==kCallerSPDisplacement) - old stack's end
5627  // [fp + 1 (==kCallerPCOffset)] - saved old ra
5628  // [fp + 0 (==kCallerFPOffset)] - saved old fp
5629  // [fp - 1 frame_type Smi
5630  // [fp - 2 (==kSPOffset)] - sp of the called function
5631  // fp - (2 + stack_space + alignment) == sp == [fp - kSPOffset] - top of the
5632  // new stack (will contain saved ra)
5633 
5634  // Save registers and reserve room for saved entry sp.
5635  daddiu(sp, sp, -2 * kPointerSize - ExitFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeFromFp);
5636  Sd(ra, MemOperand(sp, 3 * kPointerSize));
5637  Sd(fp, MemOperand(sp, 2 * kPointerSize));
5638  li(scratch, Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(frame_type)));
5639  Sd(scratch, MemOperand(sp, 1 * kPointerSize));
5640 
5641  // Set up new frame pointer.
5642  daddiu(fp, sp, ExitFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeFromFp);
5643 
5644  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
5645  Sd(zero_reg, MemOperand(fp, ExitFrameConstants::kSPOffset));
5646  }
5647 
5648  // Save the frame pointer and the context in top.
5649  ER c_entry_fp_address =
5650  ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kCEntryFPAddress, isolate());
5651  Sd(fp, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(c_entry_fp_address, no_reg));
5652 
5653  ER context_address = ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kContextAddress, isolate());
5654  Sd(cp, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(context_address, no_reg));
5655 
5656  const int frame_alignment = MacroAssembler::ActivationFrameAlignment();
5657 
5658  // Reserve place for the return address, stack space and align the frame
5659  // preparing for calling the runtime function.
5660  DCHECK_GE(stack_space, 0);
5661  Dsubu(sp, sp, Operand((stack_space + 1) * kPointerSize));
5662  if (frame_alignment > 0) {
5663  DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(frame_alignment));
5664  And(sp, sp, Operand(-frame_alignment)); // Align stack.
5665  }
5666 
5667  // Set the exit frame sp value to point just before the return address
5668  // location.
5669  daddiu(scratch, sp, kPointerSize);
5670  Sd(scratch, MemOperand(fp, ExitFrameConstants::kSPOffset));
5671 }
5672 
5673 void MacroAssembler::LeaveExitFrame(Register scratch) {
5674  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5675  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5676 
5677  using ER = ExternalReference;
5678 
5679  // Restore current context from top and clear it in debug mode.
5680  ER context_address = ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kContextAddress, isolate());
5681  Ld(cp, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(context_address, no_reg));
5682 
5683  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
5684  li(scratch, Operand(Context::kNoContext));
5685  Sd(scratch, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(context_address, no_reg));
5686  }
5687 
5688  // Clear the top frame.
5689  ER c_entry_fp_address =
5690  ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kCEntryFPAddress, isolate());
5691  Sd(zero_reg, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(c_entry_fp_address, no_reg));
5692 
5693  // Pop the arguments, restore registers, and return.
5694  mov(sp, fp); // Respect ABI stack constraint.
5695  Ld(fp, MemOperand(sp, ExitFrameConstants::kCallerFPOffset));
5696  Ld(ra, MemOperand(sp, ExitFrameConstants::kCallerPCOffset));
5697 
5698  daddiu(sp, sp, 2 * kPointerSize);
5699 }
5700 
5701 int MacroAssembler::ActivationFrameAlignment() {
5702 #if V8_HOST_ARCH_MIPS || V8_HOST_ARCH_MIPS64
5703  // Running on the real platform. Use the alignment as mandated by the local
5704  // environment.
5705  // Note: This will break if we ever start generating snapshots on one Mips
5706  // platform for another Mips platform with a different alignment.
5707  return base::OS::ActivationFrameAlignment();
5708 #else // V8_HOST_ARCH_MIPS
5709  // If we are using the simulator then we should always align to the expected
5710  // alignment. As the simulator is used to generate snapshots we do not know
5711  // if the target platform will need alignment, so this is controlled from a
5712  // flag.
5713  return v8_flags.sim_stack_alignment;
5714 #endif // V8_HOST_ARCH_MIPS
5715 }

5752 void MacroAssembler::AssertJSAny(Register object, Register map_tmp,
5753  Register tmp, AbortReason abort_reason) {
5754  if (!v8_flags.debug_code) return;
5755 
5756  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5757  DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, map_tmp, tmp));

5759

5762  GetObjectType(object, map_tmp, tmp);

5764  Branch(&ok, kUnsignedLessThanEqual, tmp, Operand(LAST_NAME_TYPE));
5765

5767 
5768  Branch(&ok, kEqual, map_tmp, RootIndex::kHeapNumberMap);
5769 
5770  Branch(&ok, kEqual, map_tmp, RootIndex::kBigIntMap);
5771 
5772  Branch(&ok, kEqual, object, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
5773 
5774  Branch(&ok, kEqual, object, RootIndex::kTrueValue);
5775 
5776  Branch(&ok, kEqual, object, RootIndex::kFalseValue);
5777 
5778  Branch(&ok, kEqual, object, RootIndex::kNullValue);
5779 
5780  Abort(abort_reason);
5781  bind(&ok);
5782 }

5925 void MacroAssembler::Float32Max(FPURegister dst, FPURegister src1,
5926  FPURegister src2, Label* out_of_line) {
5927  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5928  if (src1 == src2) {
5929  Move_s(dst, src1);
5930  return;
5931  }
5932 
5933  // Check if one of operands is NaN.
5934  CompareIsNanF32(src1, src2);
5935  BranchTrueF(out_of_line);
5936 
5937  if (kArchVariant >= kMips64r6) {
5938  max_s(dst, src1, src2);
5939  } else {
5940  Label return_left, return_right, done;
5941 
5942  CompareF32(OLT, src1, src2);
5943  BranchTrueShortF(&return_right);
5944  CompareF32(OLT, src2, src1);
5945  BranchTrueShortF(&return_left);
5946 
5947  // Operands are equal, but check for +/-0.
5948  {
5949  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5950  mfc1(t8, src1);
5951  dsll32(t8, t8, 0);
5952  Branch(&return_left, eq, t8, Operand(zero_reg));
5953  Branch(&return_right);
5954  }
5955 
5956  bind(&return_right);
5957  if (src2 != dst) {
5958  Move_s(dst, src2);
5959  }
5960  Branch(&done);
5961 
5962  bind(&return_left);
5963  if (src1 != dst) {
5964  Move_s(dst, src1);
5965  }
5966 
5967  bind(&done);
5968  }
5969 }
5970

5972  FPURegister src2) {
5973  add_s(dst, src1, src2);

5977  FPURegister src2, Label* out_of_line) {

5980  Move_s(dst, src1);
5981  return;
5982  }
5983

5995  CompareF32(OLT, src2, src1);
5996  BranchTrueShortF(&return_right);

6001  mfc1(t8, src1);
6002  dsll32(t8, t8, 0);
6003  Branch(&return_right, eq, t8, Operand(zero_reg));
6004  Branch(&return_left);
6005  }
6006 
6007  bind(&return_right);

6009  Move_s(dst, src2);
6010  }
6011  Branch(&done);
6012 
6013  bind(&return_left);
6014  if (src1 != dst) {
6015  Move_s(dst, src1);
6016  }
6017 
6018  bind(&done);
6019  }
6020 }

6127 int MacroAssembler::CalculateStackPassedWords(int num_reg_arguments,
6128  int num_double_arguments) {
6129  int stack_passed_words = 0;
6130  int num_args = num_reg_arguments + num_double_arguments;
6131 
6132  // Up to eight arguments are passed in FPURegisters and GPRegisters.
6133  if (num_args > kRegisterPassedArguments) {
6134  stack_passed_words = num_args - kRegisterPassedArguments;
6135  }
6136  stack_passed_words += kCArgSlotCount;
6137  return stack_passed_words;
6138 }
6139 
6140 void MacroAssembler::PrepareCallCFunction(int num_reg_arguments,
6141  int num_double_arguments,
6142  Register scratch) {
6143  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6144  int frame_alignment = ActivationFrameAlignment();
6145 
6146  // n64: Up to eight simple arguments in a0..a3, a4..a7, No argument slots.
6147  // O32: Up to four simple arguments are passed in registers a0..a3.
6148  // Those four arguments must have reserved argument slots on the stack for
6149  // mips, even though those argument slots are not normally used.
6150  // Both ABIs: Remaining arguments are pushed on the stack, above (higher
6151  // address than) the (O32) argument slots. (arg slot calculation handled by
6152  // CalculateStackPassedWords()).
6153  int stack_passed_arguments =
6154  CalculateStackPassedWords(num_reg_arguments, num_double_arguments);
6155  if (frame_alignment > kPointerSize) {
6156  // Make stack end at alignment and make room for num_arguments - 4 words
6157  // and the original value of sp.
6158  mov(scratch, sp);
6159  Dsubu(sp, sp, Operand((stack_passed_arguments + 1) * kPointerSize));
6160  DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(frame_alignment));
6161  And(sp, sp, Operand(-frame_alignment));
6162  Sd(scratch, MemOperand(sp, stack_passed_arguments * kPointerSize));
6163  } else {
6164  Dsubu(sp, sp, Operand(stack_passed_arguments * kPointerSize));
6165  }
6166 }
6167 
6168 void MacroAssembler::PrepareCallCFunction(int num_reg_arguments,
6169  Register scratch) {
6170  PrepareCallCFunction(num_reg_arguments, 0, scratch);
6171 }

6208 int MacroAssembler::CallCFunctionHelper(
6209  Register function, int num_reg_arguments, int num_double_arguments,
6210  SetIsolateDataSlots set_isolate_data_slots, Label* return_location) {
6211  DCHECK_LE(num_reg_arguments + num_double_arguments, kMaxCParameters);
6212  DCHECK(has_frame());
6213 
6214  Label get_pc;
6215 
6216  // Make sure that the stack is aligned before calling a C function unless
6217  // running in the simulator. The simulator has its own alignment check which
6218  // provides more information.
6219  // The argument stots are presumed to have been set up by
6220  // PrepareCallCFunction. The C function must be called via t9, for mips ABI.
6221 
6222 #if V8_HOST_ARCH_MIPS || V8_HOST_ARCH_MIPS64
6223  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
6224  int frame_alignment = base::OS::ActivationFrameAlignment();
6225  int frame_alignment_mask = frame_alignment - 1;
6226  if (frame_alignment > kPointerSize) {
6227  DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(frame_alignment));
6228  Label alignment_as_expected;
6229  {
6230  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6231  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6232  And(scratch, sp, Operand(frame_alignment_mask));
6233  Branch(&alignment_as_expected, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
6234  }
6235  // Don't use Check here, as it will call Runtime_Abort possibly
6236  // re-entering here.
6237  stop();
6238  bind(&alignment_as_expected);
6239  }
6240  }
6241 #endif // V8_HOST_ARCH_MIPS
6242 
6243  // Just call directly. The function called cannot cause a GC, or
6244  // allow preemption, so the return address in the link register
6245  // stays correct.
6246  {
6247  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
6248  if (set_isolate_data_slots == SetIsolateDataSlots::kYes) {
6249  if (function != t9) {
6250  mov(t9, function);
6251  function = t9;
6252  }
6253 
6254  // Save the frame pointer and PC so that the stack layout remains
6255  // iterable, even without an ExitFrame which normally exists between JS
6256  // and C frames. 't' registers are caller-saved so this is safe as a
6257  // scratch register.
6258  Register pc_scratch = t1;
6259  DCHECK(!AreAliased(pc_scratch, function));
6260  CHECK(root_array_available());
6261 
6262  LoadAddressPCRelative(pc_scratch, &get_pc);
6263 
6264  Sd(pc_scratch,
6265  ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kFastCCallCallerPC));
6266  Sd(fp, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kFastCCallCallerFP));
6267  }
6268 
6269  int call_pc_offset;
6270  {
6271  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
6272  Call(function);
6273  call_pc_offset = pc_offset();
6274  bind(&get_pc);
6275  if (return_location) bind(return_location);
6276 
6277  int before_offset = pc_offset();
6278  int stack_passed_arguments =
6279  CalculateStackPassedWords(num_reg_arguments, num_double_arguments);
6280 
6281  if (base::OS::ActivationFrameAlignment() > kSystemPointerSize) {
6282  Ld(sp, MemOperand(sp, stack_passed_arguments * kSystemPointerSize));
6283  } else {
6284  Daddu(sp, sp, Operand(stack_passed_arguments * kSystemPointerSize));
6285  }
6286 
6287  if (kMaxSizeOfMoveAfterFastCall > pc_offset() - before_offset) {
6288  nop();
6289  }
6290  // We assume that with the nop padding, the move instruction uses
6291  // kMaxSizeOfMoveAfterFastCall bytes. When we patch in the deopt
6292  // trampoline, we patch it in after the move instruction, so that the
6293  // stack has been restored correctly.
6294  CHECK_EQ(kMaxSizeOfMoveAfterFastCall, pc_offset() - before_offset);
6295  }
6296 
6297  if (set_isolate_data_slots == SetIsolateDataSlots::kYes) {
6298  // We don't unset the PC; the FP is the source of truth.
6299  Sd(zero_reg,
6300  ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kFastCCallCallerFP));
6301  }
6302 
6303  set_pc_for_safepoint();
6304 
6305  return call_pc_offset;
6306  }
6307 }
6308 
6309 #undef BRANCH_ARGS_CHECK

6311 void MacroAssembler::CheckPageFlag(Register object, Register scratch, int mask,
6312  Condition cc, Label* condition_met) {
6313  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6314  And(scratch, object, Operand(~MemoryChunk::GetAlignmentMaskForAssembler()));
6315  Ld(scratch, MemOperand(scratch, MemoryChunk::FlagsOffset()));
6316  And(scratch, scratch, Operand(mask));
6317  Branch(condition_met, cc, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
6318 }

6320 Register GetRegisterThatIsNotOneOf(Register reg1, Register reg2, Register reg3,
6321  Register reg4, Register reg5,
6322  Register reg6) {
6323  RegList regs = {reg1, reg2, reg3, reg4, reg5, reg6};
6324 
6325  const RegisterConfiguration* config = RegisterConfiguration::Default();
6326  for (int i = 0; i < config->num_allocatable_general_registers(); ++i) {
6327  int code = config->GetAllocatableGeneralCode(i);
6328  Register candidate = Register::from_code(code);
6329  if (regs.has(candidate)) continue;
6330  return candidate;
6331  }
6332  UNREACHABLE();
6333 }
6334 void MacroAssembler::ComputeCodeStartAddress(Register dst) {
6335  // This push on ra and the pop below together ensure that we restore the
6336  // register ra, which is needed while computing the code start address.
6337  push(ra);
6338 
6339  // The nal instruction puts the address of the current instruction into
6340  // the return address (ra) register, which we can use later on.
6341  if (kArchVariant == kMips64r6) {
6342  addiupc(ra, 1);
6343  } else {
6344  nal();
6345  nop();
6346  }
6347  int pc = pc_offset();
6348  li(dst, Operand(pc));
6349  Dsubu(dst, ra, dst);
6350 
6351  pop(ra); // Restore ra
6352 }
6353 // Check if the code object is marked for deoptimization. If it is, then it
6354 // jumps to the CompileLazyDeoptimizedCode builtin. In order to do this we need
6355 // to:
6356 // 1. read from memory the word that contains that bit, which can be found in
6357 // the flags in the referenced {Code} object;
6358 // 2. test kMarkedForDeoptimizationBit in those flags; and
6359 // 3. if it is not zero then it jumps to the builtin.
6360 //
6361 // Note: With leaptiering we simply assert the code is not deoptimized.
6362 void MacroAssembler::BailoutIfDeoptimized() {
6363  // UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6364  // Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6365  if (v8_flags.debug_code || !V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING_BOOL) {
6366  int offset =
6367  InstructionStream::kCodeOffset - InstructionStream::kHeaderSize;
6368  // LoadProtectedPointerField(
6369  // scratch, MemOperand(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister, offset));
6370  Ld(kScratchReg, MemOperand(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister, offset));
6371  Lwu(kScratchReg, FieldMemOperand(kScratchReg, Code::kFlagsOffset));
6372  }
6373 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
6374  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
6375  Label not_deoptimized;
6376  And(kScratchReg, kScratchReg,
6377  Operand(1 << Code::kMarkedForDeoptimizationBit));
6378  Branch(&not_deoptimized, eq, kScratchReg, Operand(zero_reg));
6379  Abort(AbortReason::kInvalidDeoptimizedCode);
6380  bind(&not_deoptimized);
6381  }
6382 #else
6383  And(kScratchReg, kScratchReg,
6384  Operand(1 << Code::kMarkedForDeoptimizationBit));
6385  TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kCompileLazyDeoptimizedCode, ne, kScratchReg,
6386  Operand(zero_reg));
6387 #endif
6388 }
6389 
6390 void MacroAssembler::CallForDeoptimization(Builtin target, int, Label* exit,
6391  DeoptimizeKind kind, Label* ret,
6392  Label*) {
6393  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6394  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
6395  Ld(t9,
6396  MemOperand(kRootRegister, IsolateData::BuiltinEntrySlotOffset(target)));
6397  Call(t9);
6398  DCHECK_EQ(SizeOfCodeGeneratedSince(exit),
6399  (kind == DeoptimizeKind::kLazy) ? Deoptimizer::kLazyDeoptExitSize
6400  : Deoptimizer::kEagerDeoptExitSize);
6401 }

6428 void MacroAssembler::CallJSFunction(Register function_object,
6429  uint16_t argument_count) {
6430  Register code = kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister;
6431 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
6432  Register dispatch_handle = kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister;
6433  Register parameter_count = s1;
6434  Register scratch = s2;
6435 
6436  Lw(dispatch_handle,
6437  FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kDispatchHandleOffset));
6438  LoadEntrypointAndParameterCountFromJSDispatchTable(code, parameter_count,
6439  dispatch_handle, scratch);
6440 
6441  // Force a safe crash if the parameter count doesn't match.
6442  SbxCheck(le, AbortReason::kJSSignatureMismatch, parameter_count,
6443  Operand(argument_count));
6444  Call(code);
6445 #else
6446  Ld(code, FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kCodeOffset));
6447  CallCodeObject(code, kJSEntrypointTag);
6448 #endif
6449 }

6467 void MacroAssembler::ResolveWasmCodePointer(Register target) {

6470  ExternalReference::wasm_code_pointer_table();
6471  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);

6495 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
6496 // Only used when leaptiering is disabled.
6497 void TailCallOptimizedCodeSlot(MacroAssembler* masm,
6498  Register optimized_code_entry, Register scratch1,
6499  Register scratch2) {
6500  // ----------- S t a t e -------------
6501  // -- a0 : actual argument count
6502  // -- a3 : new target (preserved for callee if needed, and caller)
6503  // -- a1 : target function (preserved for callee if needed, and caller)
6504  // -----------------------------------
6505  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(masm);
6506  DCHECK(!AreAliased(optimized_code_entry, a1, a3, scratch1, scratch2));
6507 
6508  Label heal_optimized_code_slot;
6509 
6510  // If the optimized code is cleared, go to runtime to update the optimization
6511  // marker field.
6512  __ LoadWeakValue(optimized_code_entry, optimized_code_entry,
6513  &heal_optimized_code_slot);
6514 
6515  // The entry references a CodeWrapper object. Unwrap it now.
6516  __ Ld(optimized_code_entry,
6517  FieldMemOperand(optimized_code_entry, CodeWrapper::kCodeOffset));
6518 
6519  // Check if the optimized code is marked for deopt. If it is, call the
6520  // runtime to clear it.
6521  __ TestCodeIsMarkedForDeoptimizationAndJump(optimized_code_entry, scratch1,
6522  ne, &heal_optimized_code_slot);
6523 
6524  // Optimized code is good, get it into the closure and link the closure into
6525  // the optimized functions list, then tail call the optimized code.
6526  // The feedback vector is no longer used, so reuse it as a scratch
6527  // register.
6528  __ ReplaceClosureCodeWithOptimizedCode(optimized_code_entry, a1, scratch1,
6529  scratch2);
6530 
6531  static_assert(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister == a2, "ABI mismatch");
6532  __ LoadCodeInstructionStart(a2, optimized_code_entry, kJSEntrypointTag);
6533  __ Jump(a2);
6534 
6535  // Optimized code slot contains deoptimized code or code is cleared and
6536  // optimized code marker isn't updated. Evict the code, update the marker
6537  // and re-enter the closure's code.
6538  __ bind(&heal_optimized_code_slot);
6539  __ GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(Runtime::kHealOptimizedCodeSlot);
6540 }
6541 #endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
6542 
6543 } // namespace

6562 void MacroAssembler::ReplaceClosureCodeWithOptimizedCode(
6563  Register optimized_code, Register closure, Register scratch1,
6564  Register scratch2) {
6565  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6566  DCHECK(!AreAliased(optimized_code, closure, scratch1, scratch2));
6567 
6568 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
6569  UNREACHABLE();
6570 #else
6571  // Store code entry in the closure.
6572  Sd(optimized_code, FieldMemOperand(closure, JSFunction::kCodeOffset));
6573  mov(scratch1, optimized_code); // Write barrier clobbers scratch1 below.
6574  RecordWriteField(closure, JSFunction::kCodeOffset, scratch1, scratch2,
6575  kRAHasNotBeenSaved, SaveFPRegsMode::kIgnore,
6576  SmiCheck::kOmit);
6577 #endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
6578 }
6579 
6580 void MacroAssembler::GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(
6581  Runtime::FunctionId function_id) {
6582  // ----------- S t a t e -------------
6583  // -- a0 : actual argument count
6584  // -- a1 : target function (preserved for callee)
6585  // -- a3 : new target (preserved for callee)
6586  // -----------------------------------
6587  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6588  {
6589  FrameScope scope(this, StackFrame::INTERNAL);
6590  // Push a copy of the target function, the new target and the actual
6591  // argument count.
6592  // Push function as parameter to the runtime call.
6593  SmiTag(kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
6594  Push(kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister, kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister,
6595  kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
6596 #ifdef V8_JS_LINKAGE_INCLUDES_DISPATCH_HANDLE
6597  // No need to SmiTag since dispatch handles always look like Smis.
6598  static_assert(kJSDispatchHandleShift > 0);
6599  AssertSmi(kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister);
6600  Push(kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister);
6601 #endif
6602  // Function is also the parameter to the runtime call.
6603  Push(kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister);
6604  CallRuntime(function_id, 1);
6605  // Restore target function, new target and actual argument count.
6606 #ifdef V8_JS_LINKAGE_INCLUDES_DISPATCH_HANDLE
6607  Pop(kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister);
6608 #endif
6609  Pop(kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister, kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister,
6610  kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
6611  SmiUntag(kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
6612  }
6613 
6614  static_assert(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister == a2, "ABI mismatch");
6615  LoadCodeInstructionStart(a2, v0, kJSEntrypointTag);
6616  Jump(a2);
6617 }
6618 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
6619 void MacroAssembler::LoadFeedbackVectorFlagsAndJumpIfNeedsProcessing(
6620  Register flags, Register feedback_vector, CodeKind current_code_kind,
6621  Label* flags_need_processing) {
6622  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6623  DCHECK(CodeKindCanTierUp(current_code_kind));
6624  Register scratch = t2;
6625  uint32_t flag_mask =
6626  FeedbackVector::FlagMaskForNeedsProcessingCheckFrom(current_code_kind);
6627  Lhu(flags, FieldMemOperand(feedback_vector, FeedbackVector::kFlagsOffset));
6628  And(scratch, flags, Operand(flag_mask));
6629  Branch(flags_need_processing, ne, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
6630 }
6631 
6632 void MacroAssembler::OptimizeCodeOrTailCallOptimizedCodeSlot(
6633  Register flags, Register feedback_vector) {
6634  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6635  Label maybe_has_optimized_code, maybe_needs_logging;
6636  // Check if optimized code marker is available.
6637  {
6638  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6639  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6640  And(scratch, flags,
6641  Operand(FeedbackVector::kFlagsTieringStateIsAnyRequested));
6642  Branch(&maybe_needs_logging, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
6643  }
6644 
6645  GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(Runtime::kCompileOptimized);
6646 
6647  bind(&maybe_needs_logging);
6648  {
6649  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6650  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6651  And(scratch, flags, Operand(FeedbackVector::LogNextExecutionBit::kMask));
6652  Branch(&maybe_has_optimized_code, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
6653  }
6654 
6655  GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(Runtime::kFunctionLogNextExecution);
6656 
6657  bind(&maybe_has_optimized_code);
6658  Register optimized_code_entry = flags;
6659  Ld(optimized_code_entry,
6660  FieldMemOperand(feedback_vector,
6661  FeedbackVector::kMaybeOptimizedCodeOffset));
6662  TailCallOptimizedCodeSlot(this, optimized_code_entry, t3, a5);
6663 }
6664 
6665 #endif // !V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
6666 // Calls an API function. Allocates HandleScope, extracts returned value
6667 // from handle and propagates exceptions. Clobbers C argument registers
6668 // and C caller-saved registers. Restores context. On return removes
6669 // (*argc_operand + slots_to_drop_on_return) * kSystemPointerSize
6670 // (GCed, includes the call JS arguments space and the additional space
6671 // allocated for the fast call).
6672 void CallApiFunctionAndReturn(MacroAssembler* masm, bool with_profiling,
6673  Register function_address,
6674  ExternalReference thunk_ref, Register thunk_arg,
6675  int slots_to_drop_on_return,
6676  MemOperand* argc_operand,
6677  MemOperand return_value_operand) {
6678  using ER = ExternalReference;
6679 
6680  Isolate* isolate = masm->isolate();
6681  MemOperand next_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
6682  ER::handle_scope_next_address(isolate), no_reg);
6683  MemOperand limit_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
6684  ER::handle_scope_limit_address(isolate), no_reg);
6685  MemOperand level_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
6686  ER::handle_scope_level_address(isolate), no_reg);
6687 
6688  Register return_value = v0;
6689  Register scratch = a4;
6690  Register scratch2 = a5;
6691 
6692  // Allocate HandleScope in callee-saved registers.
6693  // We will need to restore the HandleScope after the call to the API function,
6694  // by allocating it in callee-saved registers it'll be preserved by C code.
6695  Register prev_next_address_reg = s0;
6696  Register prev_limit_reg = s1;
6697  Register prev_level_reg = s2;
6698 
6699  // C arguments (kCArgRegs[0/1]) are expected to be initialized outside, so
6700  // this function must not corrupt them (return_value overlaps with
6701  // kCArgRegs[0] but that's ok because we start using it only after the C
6702  // call).
6703  DCHECK(!AreAliased(kCArgRegs[0], kCArgRegs[1], // C args
6704  scratch, scratch2, prev_next_address_reg, prev_limit_reg));
6705  // function_address and thunk_arg might overlap but this function must not
6706  // corrupted them until the call is made (i.e. overlap with return_value is
6707  // fine).
6708  DCHECK(!AreAliased(function_address, // incoming parameters
6709  scratch, scratch2, prev_next_address_reg, prev_limit_reg));
6710  DCHECK(!AreAliased(thunk_arg, // incoming parameters
6711  scratch, scratch2, prev_next_address_reg, prev_limit_reg));
6712 
6713  {
6714  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm,
6715  "Allocate HandleScope in callee-save registers.");
6716  __ Ld(prev_next_address_reg, next_mem_op);
6717  __ Ld(prev_limit_reg, limit_mem_op);
6718  __ Lw(prev_level_reg, level_mem_op);
6719  __ Addu(scratch, prev_level_reg, Operand(1));
6720  __ Sw(scratch, level_mem_op);
6721  }
6722 
6723  Label profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled, done_api_call;
6724  if (with_profiling) {
6725  __ RecordComment("Check if profiler or side effects check is enabled");
6726  __ Lb(scratch,
6727  __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kExecutionMode));
6728  __ Branch(&profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled, ne, scratch,
6729  Operand(zero_reg));
6730 #ifdef V8_RUNTIME_CALL_STATS
6731  __ RecordComment("Check if RCS is enabled");
6732  __ li(scratch, ER::address_of_runtime_stats_flag());
6733  __ Lw(scratch, MemOperand(scratch, 0));
6734  __ Branch(&profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled, ne, scratch,
6735  Operand(zero_reg));
6736 #endif // V8_RUNTIME_CALL_STATS
6737  }
6738 
6739  __ RecordComment("Call the api function directly.");
6740  __ StoreReturnAddressAndCall(function_address);
6741  __ bind(&done_api_call);
6742 
6743  Label propagate_exception;
6744  Label delete_allocated_handles;
6745  Label leave_exit_frame;
6746 
6747  __ RecordComment("Load value from ReturnValue.");
6748  __ Ld(return_value, return_value_operand);
6749 
6750  {
6751  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(
6752  masm,
6753  "No more valid handles (the result handle was the last one)."
6754  "Restore previous handle scope.");
6755  __ Sd(prev_next_address_reg, next_mem_op);
6756  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
6757  __ Lw(scratch, level_mem_op);
6758  __ Subu(scratch, scratch, Operand(1));
6759  __ Check(eq, AbortReason::kUnexpectedLevelAfterReturnFromApiCall, scratch,
6760  Operand(prev_level_reg));
6761  }
6762  __ Sw(prev_level_reg, level_mem_op);
6763  __ Ld(scratch, limit_mem_op);
6764  __ Branch(&delete_allocated_handles, ne, prev_limit_reg, Operand(scratch));
6765  }
6766 
6767  __ RecordComment("Leave the API exit frame.");
6768  __ bind(&leave_exit_frame);
6769 
6770  Register argc_reg = prev_limit_reg;
6771  if (argc_operand != nullptr) {
6772  // Load the number of stack slots to drop before LeaveExitFrame modifies sp.
6773  __ Ld(argc_reg, *argc_operand);
6774  }
6775 
6776  __ LeaveExitFrame(scratch);
6777 
6778  {
6779  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm,
6780  "Check if the function scheduled an exception.");
6781  __ LoadRoot(scratch, RootIndex::kTheHoleValue);
6782  __ Ld(scratch2, __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
6783  ER::exception_address(isolate), no_reg));
6784  __ Branch(&propagate_exception, ne, scratch, Operand(scratch2));
6785  }
6786 
6787  __ AssertJSAny(return_value, scratch, scratch2,
6788  AbortReason::kAPICallReturnedInvalidObject);
6789 
6790  if (argc_operand == nullptr) {
6791  DCHECK_NE(slots_to_drop_on_return, 0);
6792  __ Daddu(sp, sp, Operand(slots_to_drop_on_return * kSystemPointerSize));
6793  } else {
6794  // {argc_operand} was loaded into {argc_reg} above.
6795  if (slots_to_drop_on_return != 0) {
6796  __ Daddu(sp, sp, Operand(slots_to_drop_on_return * kSystemPointerSize));
6797  }
6798  __ Dlsa(sp, sp, argc_reg, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
6799  }
6800 
6801  __ Ret();
6802 
6803  if (with_profiling) {
6804  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm, "Call the api function via thunk wrapper.");
6805  __ bind(&profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled);
6806  // Additional parameter is the address of the actual callback.
6807  if (thunk_arg.is_valid()) {
6808  MemOperand thunk_arg_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
6809  IsolateFieldId::kApiCallbackThunkArgument);
6810  __ Sd(thunk_arg, thunk_arg_mem_op);
6811  }
6812  __ li(scratch, thunk_ref);
6813  __ StoreReturnAddressAndCall(scratch);
6814  __ Branch(&done_api_call);
6815  }
6816 
6817  __ RecordComment("An exception was thrown. Propagate it.");
6818  __ bind(&propagate_exception);
6819  __ TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kPropagateException);
6820 
6821  {
6822  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(
6823  masm, "HandleScope limit has changed. Delete allocated extensions.");
6824  __ bind(&delete_allocated_handles);
6825  __ Sd(prev_limit_reg, limit_mem_op);
6826  // Save the return value in a callee-save register.
6827  Register saved_result = prev_limit_reg;
6828  __ mov(saved_result, v0);
6829  __ mov(kCArgRegs[0], v0);
6830  __ PrepareCallCFunction(1, prev_level_reg);
6831  __ li(kCArgRegs[0], ER::isolate_address());
6832  __ CallCFunction(ER::delete_handle_scope_extensions(), 1);
6833  __ mov(v0, saved_result);
6834  __ jmp(&leave_exit_frame);
6835  }
6836 }
6837 
6838 } // namespace internal
6839 } // namespace v8

6842
